
				                 A man, believed to be in his 30s, drowned in a water pool at a resort in Ladybrand in the Free State on Sunday afternoon, paramedics said.
ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at 12.17pm and the fire department’s rescue team soon afterwards, ER24 spokeswoman Ineke van Huyssteen said.
“The rescue divers immediately began to search the pool and managed to retrieve the man. Unfortunately, there was nothing that could be done for the man and ER24 declared the man dead on the scene.”
– African News Agency (ANA)

